how do I strengthen my relationship with brand partners? 👇🏽
.
this year I’ve been focused on how I can best serve not only my audience, but also the business relationships in my life. it’s no secret that networking & community are extremely large pieces of landing consistent, high paying deals… so here’s what I’ve learned
.
1. Timeliness is everything ⌛  Be on time with all your deliverables. This includes getting concepts on time, turning around feedback, and (of course) being timely with the actual content delivery
.
2. Communication is KEY 🗣️ If for some reason, you can’t meet a deadline, need more time, etc. communicate early and communicate often. 9/10 times your brand partner will be understanding. It’s when you simply miss deadlines & don’t communicate that you start to burn bridges
.
3. Following the brief is actually important 📑  While companies hire influencers for doing what they do best, at the end of the day you’re producing an ad for the company – and they want it to be about them! Following a brief and aligning it with your content in a natural way is the ultimate sweet spot
.
Bonus tip – following a brief & creating aligned content opens you up to more licensing opportunities. Obviously, if the content is aligned & well produced, brands are more willing to invest more money into those assets. This is also a good reason why you should never use any copyrighted materials in your ads. Brands won’t take on the legal risk to boost that content!
.
Was this helpful? Lmk in the comments below and drop any Q’s you’ve got about the creator economy. I’d LOVE to answer them for you!

okay but hear me out… 👇🏽
.
”the stress of too many projects and tight turn arounds is triggering the ragey self harm side of my dysthymia” is a real message I sent to my team on Monday night
.
February was the most insane month of my entire career sitting just $10k shy of signing my ENTIRE 2022 business revenue in 28 days alone. Obviously I was ELATED!
.
A 6 figure MONTH? A career milestone? Companies that I love and adore that wanted to work with me on a long term basis? Every day in February was like the best kind of electricity… until the first Monday of the following month hit
.
I’d spent the entire day in high stress. Meetings that were pushed then unpushed, brands that were micromanaging my process, re-launching an entire new arm of my business, things getting added to my calendar that I didn’t agree to but was obliged to be there, etc etc etc.
.
That day I put my Slack notifications on silent, played exactly 1 song off my “Don’t Give Up On Your Dreams, Bitch” playlist, cried my eyes out for 2 minutes and 48 seconds, and sat back down at my desk. Later that night, I was driving to my moms house with rage and stress building under my skin to the point where, for the first time in a very long time, I contemplated the idea of self harm to feel anything BUT the stress induced rage I was feeling
.
at 628pm I had an offer come in with a 24 hour turn around time and I sent the above message as a response. to be completely honest, I’m proud of myself for not taking that deal and for also recognizing when and what might send me in a dysthymic episode
.
That day I also set clear boundaries with brand partners around my work process, voiced my expectations around my work environment, and was very honest with myself about what I can and cannot take on
.
here to remind you today that we’re all human, we all deserve to enforce and have our boundaries respected, and that it’s okay to take a break
.
i love y’all, i hope you’re having a wonderful day 🫶🏼

i’ve been thinking a lot about platform growth lately 📈
.
ever since i started my influencer career i had the mindset of “grow the most you can because that is what it means to be an influencer & have this job”
.
which on one hand… ya sure! having a larger platform affords lots of people great opportunities. but time and time again micro influencers & otherwise “small” creators have shown us that you don’t need 5 million followers to dominate a digital space
.
2023 so far has marked the largest income year of my career with my income so far my entire 2022 salary in Q1 alone
.
but i’ve actually been losing followers on all platforms every single day
.
now it might sound crazy to admit this bc I know someone is going to be like “ok so you’re overcharging” or “you don’t deserve it” but here’s the thing… a smaller audience that is dedicated, believes in you, and rides for you is way more important than a large audience who couldn’t give a single fuck
.
of course, I have ambitions to grow the YGK brand but I’ve stopped caring about the numbers and am focusing my energy on cultivating the community i’ve created over here instead 🤍
.
i hope this serves as a reminder to you that you can chase, catch, & achieve your dreams at any given moment and to never compare your middle to someone else’s end
.
so cheers to happiness not hurriedness, progress not perfection, loving the life you live, & living the life you love ✨ 🥂

this year i’ve decided i’m in my “i look fucking good” era!

are you into heatless curls? YES or NO 🧸 follow @yourgirlkarly for more ✨

recently i’ve been obsessed with heatless curls not only to prevent heat damaged but also to cut down the time spent getting ready in the morning

CURRENT GO-TO METHOD:
- mist lightly with water
- apply a styling foam (i love @avedacanada Nutriplensih)
- lock it in with an oil ( @mielleorganics)
- use a roller for my bangs
- thread the wrap through my roller so it stays in place
- section each side & clip one away
- start wrapping**

***wrapping hack***
wrap ONE section around the curler until you only have a tail/end piece left and THEN add in another section of hair. i found this helped curling all of my hair vs just the front sections which is the look i prefer

PS my hair wrap is @emeraldbellaco & my extensions are @luxyhair and you can use code LX-YOURGIRLKARLY for $$$ off your extensions!

share this with a friend & comment your heatless curl hacks below! 🎀

hey, it’s YGK! ❤️‍🔥 it’s been a hot minute since i’ve re-introduced myself on here so let’s get to know each other!
.

coffee bar makeover in #YGKASA ☕

if you follow along on stories y’all already know how I feel about this coffee bar makeover but if you didn’t catch it let me break it down for you….

keep in mind @rhondacraze & I started this entire makeover back in JULY… okay?!

- the doors were so covered in varnish we had to strip them a total of 3 times
- the little ridges of the recessed doors never fully stripped even after multiple rounds & scraping
- we tried to stain them (darker) anyways….
- not all of the door took the stain & the orange oak was still showing through
- we tried to paint wash it white and also a similar brown to block the orange colour and that ALSO didn’t work

i put this project down after that for a HOT minute and decided to paint them green. You’d think this was the end of it all but….

- the painting actually went fine thank the lord
- i added new knobs to all the doors but ONE got stuck, stripped the screw, and is now hanging loosely on the door and I can’t get it off
- the plugs that attach the hinges to the door are so old and loose that not every screw completely went back in each door
- i kicked over the little container of screws (which would have been fine) BUT I also haven’t replaced the baseboards in the kitchen so 4 of them fell into the subfloor between the hardwood and the wall and I had to pick them out with pliers

and if that wasn’t enough… my Apple Watch had the AUDACITY to tell me I needed to stand for the hour after taking apart and putting together the coffee bar 84786 times in the hour

ANYWAYS… she’s cute! she’s (almost) done! and I honestly love the green! What are you thoughts?? Would love to know in the comments! 💚

welcome to #YGKitchen! today we’re making Cinnamon Bun Waffles 🤎 🍽️

SO very excited to bring you this brand new series where I share with you all of the recipes I’m cooking, foods I love making, and new things I’m trying in my kitchen

in 2019 I wrote down “cooking” on my list of 100 things that make me happy even though I wasn’t really cooking or exploring much in the kitchen but I’m SO glad I did

Over the years I’ve become more confident in the kitchen, been able to share meals as a love language, and explored things I never would have thought I’d make (hello making my own bread??)

so join me for this new series where I welcome you into my kitchen and we make fun things, hard things, yummy things, and everything in between… together!

RECIPE (save this for later):

Waffles:
2 1/2 cups flour
2 tbsp sugar
1 1/4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt
1 1/4 cup milk
3 tbsp butter

Filling:
2 tbsp butter
1 tbsp cinnamon
2/3 cup white or brown sugar

1. whisk together dry ingredients
2. combine milk and butter, add to dry ingredients
3. mix until dough is formed (it will be slightly sticky but not coming off on your hands sticky)
4. flour your countertop and roll out into a rectangle
5. combine filling ingredients in a bowl, spread across dough
6. roll your dough up from left to right
7. cut your dough into 2” ish slices
8. cook in your waffle iron
9. Enjoy!

**I usually make a batch of these by cooking them all and then freezing the cooked waffles. When I want one, I’ll pop it out of the freezer and crisp it in the toaster!
